# Still — @still/ext-chromium build-time env (Vite `import.meta.env`, baked in by `wxt build`).
#
# Copy to `packages/ext-chromium/.env` and fill in. NEVER commit a real value — only this template
# is tracked (.gitignore ignores `.env.*` and excepts `.env.example`). Legend as in the root
# .env.example ([loop-ok] etc.).
#
# Fail-safe build-mode gate (docs/solutions/security-issues/gate-production-trust-by-build-mode.md):
# leave these BLANK and the built extension simply ships WITHOUT the auth/purchase spine and
# without the OTA rule-set fetch — the popup renders the explanatory paywall (no sign-in, no
# checkout CTA) and the bundled rule seed keeps applying. There is deliberately NO dev fallback.

# [loop-ok] Public Supabase project URL + anon key (safe in client bundles; RLS is the real
# boundary). Powers the background-owned Supabase session (email-OTP sign-in, create-web-checkout,
# reconcile-entitlement, settings sync) and the signed rule-set refresh.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
